  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">School Reconstruction in Oaxaca</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">After one year of the 8.2-degree earthquake in Mexico, 170 children from the community of Salina Cruz, Oaxaca, lost their school, we want to provide them with a safe and resilient place that will allow them to continue their education and provide better opportunities for their future. The project is considered completed in 8 months. The scope is reconstruction: 7 classrooms, office, library and some parts of the perimeter wall; retrofit 4 more classrooms and repair the bathrooms.</narrative>
  </description>
